        public void setExposureType(java.lang.String exposureType)
        This is a setter method for setting the exposure type which has a condition to accept the values "D" for direct exposure or "I" for indirect exposure. It throws an IllegalArgumentException with the appropriate message - "Invalid Exposure type" within the setExposure Type method if the supplied exposure type is not "D" and not "I".
